+## Benchmark Results
+
+See [MALLOC-BENCHMARK-REPORT.md](MALLOC-BENCHMARK-REPORT.md) for a comprehensive
+benchmark comparison of all backends with recommendations for different use cases.
+
+### Original mimalloc vs glibc benchmarks (for reference)
+
+All benchmarks were run on the same machine, same kernel, same compiler
+(`gcc 13`), with both glibc variants built with identical flags (`-O2`,
+`--disable-werror`).
+
+### bench-malloc-simple
+
+This benchmark measures the cost of a malloc+free cycle for varying
+allocation sizes and allocation-batch counts. Times are in hardware
+performance-counter ticks per malloc+free pair (lower is better).
+
+| Scenario              | Size  |   glibc |  mimalloc |  Speedup |
+|-----------------------|------:|--------:|----------:|---------:|
+| ST, 25 allocs         |    16 |    48.6 |      21.9 |   2.22x  |
+| ST, 25 allocs         |    64 |    48.9 |      23.7 |   2.06x  |
+| ST, 25 allocs         |   256 |    48.1 |      27.2 |   1.76x  |
+| ST, 25 allocs         |  1024 |    57.3 |      25.3 |   2.27x  |
+| ST, 25 allocs         |  4096 |    94.3 |     101.1 |   0.93x  |
+| ST, 400 allocs        |    16 |    83.6 |      19.7 |   4.25x  |
+| ST, 400 allocs        |    64 |    84.5 |      22.2 |   3.80x  |
+| ST, 400 allocs        |   256 |    84.6 |      31.6 |   2.68x  |
+| ST, 400 allocs        |  1024 |  2526.2 |      59.2 |  42.66x  |
+| ST, 400 allocs        |  4096 | 14024.4 |     142.7 |  98.30x  |
+| ST, 1600 allocs       |    16 |    84.3 |      20.1 |   4.19x  |
+| ST, 1600 allocs       |   256 |  1046.8 |      34.6 |  30.26x  |
+| ST, 1600 allocs       |  4096 | 13848.8 |     164.6 |  84.15x  |
+| MT, 25 allocs         |    16 |    64.1 |      22.1 |   2.90x  |
+| MT, 1600 allocs       |    16 |   144.3 |      19.8 |   7.29x  |
+| MT, 1600 allocs       |  1024 |  3474.6 |      63.1 |  55.05x  |
+| Thread arena, 25      |    16 |    64.4 |      23.4 |   2.75x  |
+| Thread arena, 1600    |  4096 |  6270.9 |     168.2 |  37.29x  |
+
+**Key observations:**
+
+- For small allocations (16–256 bytes, ≤25 in flight), mimalloc is **2–3×
+  faster** than ptmalloc2.
+- For larger working sets (400–1600 concurrent allocations) and larger
+  sizes (≥256 bytes), ptmalloc2's performance degrades dramatically while
+  mimalloc stays near-constant. This is because glibc's allocator falls
+  back to `mmap`/`munmap` system calls for large allocations whereas
+  mimalloc manages its own arena pool and recycles segments. Speedups of
+  **30–98×** are observed in these scenarios.
+- The one case where glibc is marginally faster (0.93×) is 25 concurrent
+  page-sized (4096-byte) allocations in single-threaded mode — a narrow
+  sweet spot for ptmalloc2's mmap-based fast path.
+
+### bench-malloc-thread
+
+This benchmark runs a mixed random-size workload (4–32768 bytes) across
+varying thread counts. `time_per_iteration` is in ticks (lower is better).
+
+| Threads | glibc ticks/iter | mimalloc ticks/iter | Speedup | glibc RSS (KB) | mimalloc RSS (KB) |
+|--------:|-----------------:|--------------------:|--------:|---------------:|------------------:|
+|       1 |             36.2 |                25.1 |  1.44x  |          2,236 |             6,560 |
+|       4 |             40.2 |                28.4 |  1.42x  |         10,740 |            30,264 |
+|       8 |             41.2 |                30.4 |  1.36x  |         18,916 |            54,236 |
+|      16 |             46.2 |                33.6 |  1.38x  |         29,496 |           103,204 |
+
+**Key observations:**
+
+- mimalloc is consistently **1.36–1.44× faster** than ptmalloc2 under a
+  realistic mixed-size threaded workload.
+- The speedup is fairly constant across thread counts, showing both
+  allocators scale linearly.
+- mimalloc uses approximately **3× more RSS**. This is mimalloc's well-known
+  space-for-speed trade-off: it pre-commits larger arena segments and
+  does not aggressively return pages to the OS.
+
+### Summary
+
+| Metric                            | Winner    | Notes                          |
+|-----------------------------------|-----------|--------------------------------|
+| Small-alloc throughput            | mimalloc  | 2–4× faster                   |
+| Large-working-set throughput      | mimalloc  | 30–98× faster                 |
+| Multi-threaded throughput         | mimalloc  | ~1.4× faster                  |
+| Memory footprint (RSS)           | glibc     | ~3× lower RSS                 |
+| Page-sized alloc, low concurrency | glibc     | Marginally faster (~1.07×)     |
+
